2 unit(s) Pork Chops, bone-in
250 g Red Potato
1 tbsp Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
7 g Cilantro
7 g Parsley
1 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
1 unit(s) Red Onion
1 unit(s) Green Bell Pepper
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
4 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Remove any brown spots, then cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
To a parchment-lined baking sheet, add potatoes and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Season with half the Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend, salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast in the middle of the oven for 22-25 min, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden-brown.

Finely chop cilantro and parsley.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Core, then cut peppers into 1/4-inch slices.
Peel, then cut half the red onion into 1/4-inch slices. Finely chop the remaining onion.
Add peppers, sliced onion and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to an unlined baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Set aside.

In a medium bowl, whisk together vinegar, 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) oil, parsley, cilantro, 1 tsp (2 tsp) garlic, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar and finely chopped onion.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Set aside.

Pat pork dry with paper towels.
Season with salt, pepper and remaining Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium. When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil and pork. Pan-fry pork for 2-3 min per side, until golden.
Transfer pork to the baking sheet with peppers and onions. Roast in the middle of the oven for 8-10 min, until cooked through.**

In a small bowl, add the mayo and remaining garlic.
Season with salt and pepper.

Divide pork, potatoes and veggies between plates.
Spoon chimichurri over the pork.
Serve garlic mayo on the side for dipping.